    expertInsights: "Cricket pundits are weighing in on today's monumental day. \"The pressure on RCB in the Eliminator will be immense,\" notes veteran cricket analyst Rohan Sharma. \"Their batting depth will be tested, and their bowlers will need to be at their absolute best to contain KKR, and then potentially MI, to reach the final against a formidable GT side that's had time to regroup.\" Sports economist Dr. Anjali Singh adds, \"This double-header format, while demanding on players, is a dream for broadcasters and advertisers. The sheer volume of eyeballs and the narrative of RCB's quest for glory versus GT's consistent performance creates a perfect storm for engagement.\" She also highlighted the tactical battle between RCB's aggressive top-order and GT's disciplined bowling unit as the key determinant for the final.",
